\":721,\"repo\":\"pardahlman/RawRabbit\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A modern .NET Core library for RabbitMQ.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T23:17:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Bindings in Other Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ring-lang.sourceforge.net/doc/qt.html\">Ring (via RingQt)</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/ring-lang/ring/tree/master/extensions/ringqt\">:octocat:</a> - I've never heard of this language either, honestly.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:39:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code.qt.io\">Source Code</a> - Browse the various source trees that comprise the Qt project.  Has mirrors at several GitHub organizations:\n<ul>\n<li>Qt <a href=\"https://github.com/qt\">:octocat:</a></li>\n<li>Qt Project <a href=\"https://github.com/qtproject\">:octocat:</a></li>\n<li>Qt Labs <a href=\"https://github.com/qt-labs\">:octocat:</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:36:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.virtualbox.org\">VirtualBox</a> <a href=\"https://www.virtualbox.org/browser/vbox/trunk\">📦</a> - Virtualization software for x86/64 processors.  The bundled GUI uses Qt.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:24:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.qt.io\">Official Website</a> - The official website for the Qt framework.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io\">Qt Documentation</a> - Official Qt documentation.  Massive and comprehensive.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://bugreports.qt.io\">Qt Bug Tracker</a> - If you think you've found a bug with Qt or one of its related projects, report it here (or see if someone else already has).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://forum.qt.io\">Qt Forum</a> - If e-mail's not your thing, then you might also consider getting help or sharing knowledge on the forums.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wiki.qt.io\">Qt Wiki</a> - The premier source for user-contributed Qt knowledge.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Unofficial</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.qtforum.org\">QtForum.org</a> - Not to be confused with the official <a href=\"https://forum.qt.io\">Qt forum</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.qt.io/ide\">Qt Creator</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qtproject/qt-creator\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/qtproject/qt-creator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1867,\"repo\":\"qtproject/qt-creator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - By no means does Qt lock you into its provided IDE, but its firm integration with the framework makes it a good sell.  Among other things, it provides a UI designer, modeling tools, a documentation browser, and great QML support if you're into that sort of thing.  There's also a plugin system, but third-party plugins are unfortunately scarce.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qtdesigner-manual.html\">Qt Designer</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qt/qttools/tree/dev/src/designer\">:octocat:</a> - If you'd rather just design the interfaces and let someone else hook them up to logic, the GUI designer is available as a separate application.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qtassistant-index.html\">Qt Assistant</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qt/qttools/tree/dev/src/assistant\">:octocat:</a> - So is the documentation viewer, for that matter.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/qtinstallerframework\">Qt Installer Framework</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qtproject/installer-framework\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/qtproject/installer-framework\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">147</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":147,\"repo\":\"qtproject/installer-framework\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Nobody seems to talk about this, but Qt also provides a way to write an installer for your application.  Does not support creation of macOS disk images, app bundles, or Linux packages, so be mindful of that when considering your project's distribution.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/osx-deployment.html\"><code>macdeployqt</code></a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qt/qttools/tree/dev/src/macdeployqt\">:octocat:</a> - Generates macOS application bundles for Qt projects.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/emulator\">Emulator</a> - Don't forget about Qt's mobile support!</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Third-Party Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.kdab.com/development-resources/qt-tools/gammaray\">GammaRay</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/KDAB/GammaRay\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/KDAB/GammaRay\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1248,\"repo\":\"KDAB/GammaRay\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Powerful debugger and general inspection tool for Qt-built software.  Lets you inspect and manipulate the <code>QObject</code> hierarchy, view object properties, edit widgets at runtime, and far, <em>far</em> more.  A two-sentence blurb can't do it justice, seriously check it out.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.kdab.com/category/blogs\">KDAB</a> - <em>Another</em> consulting firm that specializes in Qt.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JcoFk_PVhdk\">GammaRay: Taking a deep look into your Qt application</a> - Talk about <a href=\"https://www.kdab.com/development-resources/qt-tools/gammaray\">GammaRay</a> and how it can help you dissect your Qt applications.  Talk given at QtCon 2016 by <a href=\"https://github.com/vkrause\">Volker Krause</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dcSsjxhazu0\">Multithreading with Qt</a> - I want to make my application do more than once thing at once.  What could possibly go wrong?  Talk given at QtCon 2016 by <a href=\"https://github.com/dangelog\">Giuseppe D'Angelo</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L4NClVxqdMw\">Linux perf for Qt developers</a> - How to make your Qt application faster, Linux-style.  Talk given at QtCon 2016 by <a href=\"https://github.com/milianw\">Milian Wolff</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:22:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Conventions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Any list item with an OctoCat :octocat: has a GitHub repo or organization; click on it to see the source code!</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:17:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Conventions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>List items with this 📦 icon have source code hosted elsewhere.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T20:17:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.qt.io/ide\">Qt Creator</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qtproject/qt-creator\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/qtproject/qt-creator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1867,\"repo\":\"qtproject/qt-creator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Something something eating your own dog food. Listed in the <a href=\"#official-tools\">official tools</a>, but not listing it here doesn't feel right.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T19:47:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qtlinguist-index.html\">Qt Linguist</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qt/qttools/tree/dev/src/linguist\">:octocat:</a> - Qt provides excellent internationalization/localization support, and this tool is very much responsible for it.  Write translatable strings in your code with special macros, and this tool will aggregate them all for you so you or your translator(s) can broaden your software's audience.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T18:57:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cmake.org\">CMake</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/Kitware/CMake\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Kitware/CMake\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5153,\"repo\":\"Kitware/CMake\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The closest thing to a standard C++ build system out there. The bundled GUI uses Qt.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T18:57:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen\">Doxygen</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/doxygen/doxygen\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/doxygen/doxygen\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4366,\"repo\":\"doxygen/doxygen\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The most popular documentation generator for C++, though it supports other languages as well.  The bundled GUI uses Qt.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T18:57:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.mapeditor.org\">Tiled</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/bjorn/tiled\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bjorn/tiled\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9133,\"repo\":\"bjorn/tiled\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Perhaps the world's most popular tilemap editor.  Suitable for level design in games.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T18:57:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=%23qt%2C%23qt-quick%2C%23qt-creator%2C%23qt-chat\">IRC</a> - For real-time chat with other Qt developers and users.  The most popular channels are on Freenode, and include <code>#qt</code>, <code>#qt-quick</code>, <code>#qt-creator</code>, and <code>#qt-chat</code>.\n<ul>\n<li>For a full list of Qt-related IRC channels, see <a href=\"https://wiki.qt.io/Online_Communities#IRC_channels\">here</a>.</li>\n<li>Note that the linked webchat client is <em>not</em> a part of the Qt project, and is provided by the author of this list for convenience only.  These channels can be accessed through any IRC client.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T18:21:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codereview.qt-project.org\">Qt Code Review</a> - See how the Qt maintainers ensure their code is well-written.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T18:13:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Friz-zy/awesome-linux-containers","categoryHTML":"<h2>Operating Systems</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://coreos.com/\">CoreOs</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-10-16T15:31:04.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Friz-zy/awesome-linux-containers","categoryHTML